args:
Disturbing news of a secret weapon being held
in the Chairman's office spurs Ranzal, Louise,
and Mercury to attempt an infiltration. But when
they're stopped by the guards outside Emile's
office, our heroes find themselves in crisis!
How do you suppose our academy trio is\nfaring?
I'm worried about them, I admit.\nI pray they'll return safely soon.
Agreed. And with any luck, their\ninvestigation will have borne fruit.
Heh. You're not half bad...for a kid.
Oh, right. Forgot about that. So, level with\nme, palâ€”you really THAT into Louise?
I am! I want her head pats and, if\npossible, a moderately tight hug!
Okay, look. I'll clue you in on somethin'.
She's got a little brother, and she's like a\nmother hen with the kid. Overprotective\nain't the half of it.
He gets hugs on tap.\nA veritable hug buffet.
What?! I'm not too proud to confess I am\nEXTREMELY jealous of this brother! And of\nyou, for knowing top-secret Louise intel!
Would you both PLEASE knock it off\nalready?!
Grk! I've gone and upset her...
And yet, her sharp words somehow\nmake me feel...happy? Tingly, even.\nTruly, this must be love!
Wow, you can see the little deviant's mind\nwarping in real time. Just what kinda man\nis this kid gonna grow into?
A thought I'm trying very hard not to have.\nRanzal! With me, NOW.

Rgh... I'd give anything to be manhandled
and dragged around by Louise like that.
Call me a sandwich, because I am peanut
butter and JELLY over here!
Those two must really be...\nNo. I refuse to concede!
We make our move today after school, but\nyou've been goofing off all day. Do you\nunderstand what's at stake here?
Sure I do. And I'm ready for it. Don't YOU\ngo gettin' so wound up about it you drop\nthe ball.
The area around the chairman's office is\noff-limits to kids. Even faculty can't get in\nwithout Emile's say-so.
Not to mention the armed patrol out front. I\nhope we're able to get in without incident.
Incident or no, we gotta get inside,\nso be ready for anything.
Right. These children's safety hinges\non us completing this mission.
Let's do all we can for them, Ranzal.
All right, it's go time.\nThe chairman's office is up ahead, yeah?
Yes, according to the other faculty.\nThough what awaits us there is a\ncomplete unknown.
Whatever it is, we just need to not get\ncaught. Come, let's move!
I-I thought I heard s-s-somebody coming\nthis way... H-heeey! I-is anybody there?!\nI-if you are, you hafta say so!
What's our move? If we stay here,\nwe'll be discovered!
Punch him out and walk on by?
The operation has only just begun. I would\nprefer to avoid causing a scene if possible.
I'll serve as a distraction to draw him\naway. Use that time to slip past.
A new teacher freshly arrived on campus\nfinding herself lost is hardly unthinkable.

Plus, for what comes next, if any of us 
were to be caught by imperial soldiers,
you two are more likely to make it out
unscathed.
A pair of mischievous children are better\nsuited for the infiltration than a nosy adult.
True 'nuff. They'd lecture the hell outta\nus kids, but it's hard to think they'd\ndo anything too drastic.
Factoring all of that in, I believe it's\nmost logical for me to handle this.\nI ask that you trust me.
We do. Be safe, and good luck!
(Why in the world is he so frightened?\nI haven't done a thing. Yet.)
S-stay back! I-I-I taste terrible!\nDon't eat meeeee!
She really exists... The academy legend:\nthe ghost of the empty classroom!
She must be angry 'cause I read those\nlibrary books without properly checking\nthem out first and now I'm gonna DIIIE!
(Ahhh. He's mistaken me for some ghost.\nVery well, then...)
(I'm not entirely sure how human ghosts\nare meant to sound, but... Something like\nthis, perhaps?)
Heh heh heh, yesss... I am the ghost of the\nempty classroom, and your sssoul looks...\nssscrumptious!
Um, hello? Shouldn't you be running?
They may be the enemy, but I'm beginning\nto worry for the Dyrenell Empire.
Still, it would cause a commotion if\na guard were found unconscious.
I suppose I should deliver him\nto the nurse's office. Up we go...
Rrgh, it's no fair havin' to do this on stubby\nkid legs! We can't outrun him much longer!
Let's split up. As long as one of us makes\nit through safely, that's all that matters.
Nrrrgh... Run in two different directions,\nwill you?!
Times like these, you gotta go where\nthe real action leads you! THIS WAY!
(I could keep running for the woods...but\nwandering a fiend-infested forest alone in\na child's body is far more dangerous.)
(The jig is up. I'll just have to surrender.)
I hope you're unharmed, Miss Louise.
Ryu! Louise's prisoner of love, and a boy\nvery eager for head pats and hair ruffles!!!
Uhhh...okay? I don't really get it, but\nI like your passion, kid! You got moxie!
Go on, Miss Louise. Leave this to me.
You have a task to see through, don't you?
Behind the main hallâ€”that was you?
Yes. So go, and do whatever it is you must.
I can't just leave you here!
Please... Allow me to play the hero today.\nThe chance to look good in front of you is\nworth any punishment.
Aaah, this kid gets it! He GETS it! This is\nsome peak youth drama right here! YES!
Er... Very well. Thank you, Ryu.\nBut promise me you'll stay safe!
Hey, whoa! Waaait a second.\nWhere's she think she's running off to?!
I shall defend Miss Louise with my life!\nDo your worst, sir... HAAAH!
*huff* *pant* Finally made it.\nThis has gotta be Emile's office.
Guess I'll start by diggin' up any\ndocs I can find about the academy.
Once I've got those, I'll get to\nlookin' for this secret weapon of...
Yes. Thanks to your little distraction,\nI was able to simply walk right in.
Guess we wound up givin' 'em the run-\naround and broke their security formation.\nDidn't plan that, but hey, a win's a win.
I only made it here in one piece thanks to\nRyu.
What, that shrimp with the slightly creepy\ncrush on you?
The same. Recall how we worried earlier\nthat we'd been overheard behind the\nschool building?
Well, we were. By Ryu.\nAnd thanks to that, he came to my aid.
No kiddin'? With all the ï¼‚head pats and\nhand squeezesï¼‚ talk, I pegged him as less\nof a doer and more of a swooner.
Shows what I know.\nKid's a man's man.
I'll admit I was a bit moved.
But will he be all right?
He'll probably get chewed out and thrown\nin detention for a month, but I'm sure he'll\nconsider it a badge of honor.
Now let's make sure our little loverboy's\nsacrifice doesn't go to waste and get our\nrears in gear findin' this stuff.
Agreed. Let's split up and search.
WHAT THE HECK AM I LOOKIN' AT?!
